Detailed Description

cvmx_pki_cl::_pcam::_term#

This register configures the match side of the PCAM. PKI hardware is opaque as to the use of the 16 bits of CAM data; the split between TERM and STYLE is defined by the parse engine.

For each legal j and k, PKI_CL(i)_PCAM(j)_TERM(k) must be configured identically for i=0..1.
